HEADWORD: Obrogate
<hw>Ob"ro*gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obrogatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>obrogare</ets> to obrogate.]</ety>
<def>To annul indirectly by enacting a new and contrary law, instead of
by expressly abrogating or repealing the old one.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

